    "questions": [],
    "assumptions": [
      "Low-kappa warning uses a fixed threshold of mean kappa < 0.4 (the Landis & Koch 'fair or worse' boundary); at or below it the cluster's value renders in a warning/amber style.",
      "The metric shown is the unweighted mean of pairwise Cohen's kappa across all member pairs in the cluster.",
      "Singleton clusters (one model) and clusters where no member pair has a computable kappa show a neutral placeholder (em dash), not a warning.",
      "The overlay is computed entirely on the web client from the pairwiseKappaMap already built in ModelsGroups.tsx from the modelAgreementOnTradeoffs query \u2014 no API, GraphQL schema, codegen, or migration changes.",
      "The overlay renders only in 'log-odds' and 'win-rate' data-source modes (not 'kappa-agreement', which would be circular) and only in 'groups' display mode (not 'individual', which has no clusters).",
      "While pairwiseKappaMap is still loading, cluster cards render without the overlay line \u2014 no error, no layout thrash."
    ],
    "summary": "Add an internal-kappa diagnostic overlay to the Model Groups page. When models are grouped by log-odds value profiles, each cluster card shows the mean pairwise Cohen's kappa across its members, with a warning style when it is low \u2014 surfacing clusters that look alike on paper but behave differently on individual prompts. Web-only; the pairwise kappa matrix is already loaded on the page but not passed to the cluster component.",
    "updated_at": 1778741696,
    "answers": {},
    "non_goals": [
      "No reverse overlay (profile spread per kappa cluster in kappa-agreement mode) \u2014 separate follow-up.",
      "No API-side caching of internal kappa in clusterAnalysisByMethod \u2014 separate follow-up only if per-render compute becomes a perf problem.",
      "No changes to the clustering algorithm, linkage options, distance methods, or data sources themselves.",
      "No new GraphQL fields, schema changes, codegen, or DB migration."
    ],
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "In log-odds or win-rate mode with grouped display, each cluster card shows its mean internal Cohen's kappa.",
      "Clusters with mean internal kappa below 0.4 render that value in a visually distinct warning style.",
      "Singleton clusters and clusters with no computable pairwise kappa show a neutral placeholder instead of a warning.",
      "In kappa-agreement mode and in individual display mode, no internal-kappa overlay is rendered.",
      "The Model Groups help panel explains what internal kappa means and how to read the warning.",
      "No API, GraphQL schema, codegen, or migration changes are made; web lint, test, and build all pass."
    ],
    "unresolved": []
  },
